gui.common

Interface IModel

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Item, Model, Product, ProductGroup, StorageUnit

    public interface IModel
    IModel defines functionality that is supported by all models in the program.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isSaved()
      Returns true if the model is saved in the vault, false otherwise.
      boolean isValid()
      Returns true if the model is able to be saved to the vault, false otherwise.
      Result save()
      If the Model has been validated then it must be saved.
      Result validate()
      Validates if the model is in a savable state.

    • Method Detail

      • isSaved

      • isValid

        Returns true if the model is able to be saved to the vault, false otherwise.

      • validate

        Validates if the model is in a savable state.

      • save

        Result save()
        If the Model has been validated then it must be saved. This should always return a good result as you should validate before you save.
